{"metadata": {"page_hash": "991b4135fdf96e2378ccd93c22b935584b848350b90dde8a8a6841af96272a6d", "original_filename": "aviation_instructors_handbook.pdf", "page_no": 13, "num_pages": 228, "original_width": 612.15997, "original_height": 792.06, "coco_width": 1025, "coco_height": 1025, "collection": "faa_regulations", "doc_category": "laws_and_regulations"}, "form": [{"id_box": 597056, "box": [61.5123935660151, 52.4870243415902, 158.4543317982716, 15.822717660278272], "id_box_line": 0, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 52.4870243415902, 158.4543317982716, 15.822717660278272], "text": "Severity of an Event ", "category": "Section-header", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Times,BoldItalic", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597057, "box": [61.5123935660151, 292.9943463878999, 38.54095294731538, 15.822704719339413], "id_box_line": 14, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 292.9943463878999, 38.54095294731538, 15.822704719339413], "text": "Risk ", "category": "Section-header", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Times,BoldItalic", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597058, "box": [61.5123935660151, 753.3723341666034, 249.56996453067646, 14.40383430548195], "id_box_line": 37, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 753.3723341666034, 249.56996453067646, 14.40383430548195], "text": "Flight Risk Assessment Tools ", "category": "Section-header", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Arial,Bold", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597059, "box": [61.5123935660151, 838.7137622149837, 219.70563633881514, 15.822665896523006], "id_box_line": 41, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 838.7137622149837, 219.70563633881514, 15.822665896523006], "text": "Why Should I Use a FRAT? ", "category": "Section-header", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Times,BoldItalic", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597060, "box": [489.89562278957897, 982.8167478473853, 38.06032678026952, 14.231146535615984], "id_box_line": 47, "box_line": [489.89562278957897, 982.8167478473853, 38.06032678026952, 14.231146535615984], "text": "1-10 ", "category": "Page-footer", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Calibri", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597061, "box": [61.5123935660151, 903.1320021526146, 900.6108791301723, 43.41789018508699], "id_box_line": 44, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 903.1320021526146, 900.6108791301723, 14.27490114385273], "text": "Just thinking about this task may not consider the actual risk exposure. We may allow our personal desires to manipulate our risk ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597061, "box": [61.5123935660151, 903.1320021526146, 900.6108791301723, 43.41789018508699], "id_box_line": 45, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 917.7034927909501, 900.5308596052105, 14.274899849758853], "text": "assessment in order to meet personal goals. A formal process using pen and paper gives a perspective on the entire risk picture and is ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597061, "box": [61.5123935660151, 903.1320021526146, 900.6108791301723, 43.41789018508699], "id_box_line": 46, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 932.2749821351917, 275.4980319931733, 14.274910202509915], "text": "a good way to make a thorough analysis. ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597062, "box": [61.51234165964821, 858.9956297502714, 900.5241804278706, 28.859302956846705], "id_box_line": 42, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 858.9956297502714, 900.5241285215037, 14.274903732040514], "text": "\u201cIn the thick\u201d is no time to try to mitigate a potentially hazardous outcome. When preparing for a flight or maintenance task, pilots ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597062, "box": [61.51234165964821, 858.9956297502714, 900.5241804278706, 28.859302956846705], "id_box_line": 43, "box_line": [61.51234165964821, 873.5800289750777, 626.0941303055147, 14.274903732040514], "text": "and maintenance technicians may set aside time to stop and think about the hazards involved. ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597063, "box": [61.5123935660151, 772.4466309370503, 900.4423676216528, 43.41789794965027], "id_box_line": 38, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 772.4466309370503, 896.4746616803446, 14.274916672979288], "text": "Because every flight has some level of risk, it is critical that pilots can differentiate, in advance, between a low risk flight and a high-", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597063, "box": [61.5123935660151, 772.4466309370503, 900.4423676216528, 43.41789794965027], "id_box_line": 39, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 787.0181151049162, 900.4423676216528, 14.274916672979344], "text": "risk flight, establish a review process, and develop risk mitigation strategies. A Flight Risk Analysis Tool (FRAT) enables proactive ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597063, "box": [61.5123935660151, 772.4466309370503, 900.4423676216528, 43.41789794965027], "id_box_line": 40, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 801.5896122137211, 848.3494894316593, 14.274916672979316], "text": "hazard identification, is easy to use, and can visually depict risk. It is a tool many pilots use to make better go/no-go decisions. ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597064, "box": [61.5123935660151, 687.0881855541247, 900.4672994217506, 43.43080006565157], "id_box_line": 34, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 687.0881855541247, 900.4627952886235, 14.274916672979316], "text": "After all mitigating steps have been completed, you may confront the possibility that a flight cannot be made or continued for a ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Times", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597064, "box": [61.5123935660151, 687.0881855541247, 900.4672994217506, 43.43080006565157], "id_box_line": 35, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 701.6725718379921, 900.4672994217506, 14.274916672979316], "text": "variety of reasons not only for yourself but also for your passengers. Remember that many pilots have ignored or failed to mitigate ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Times", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597064, "box": [61.5123935660151, 687.0881855541247, 900.4672994217506, 43.43080006565157], "id_box_line": 36, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 716.244056005858, 548.9788821049503, 14.274929613918118], "text": "serious and high-risk hazards, and a tragic fatal accident is all too often the result. ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Times", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597065, "box": [61.5123935660151, 530.6840248844784, 900.5856459382666, 43.43077418377396], "id_box_line": 26, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 530.6840248844784, 900.5723512107463, 14.274877850162909], "text": "Risk mitigation often begins days, sometimes weeks, before a planned flight. For example, a pilot flying a single-engine piston ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597065, "box": [61.5123935660151, 530.6840248844784, 900.5856459382666, 43.43077418377396], "id_box_line": 27, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 545.268398227407, 900.5856459382666, 14.274890791101654], "text": "aircraft without ice protection lives in the Pacific Northwest and is planning a trip in January for a scheduled speech. While keeping ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597065, "box": [61.5123935660151, 530.6840248844784, 900.5856459382666, 43.43077418377396], "id_box_line": 28, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 559.8399082771507, 724.977850560859, 14.274890791101654], "text": "the long-range weather forecast in mind, planning in advance gives the pilot several options to mitigate risk: ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597066, "box": [61.5123935660151, 386.50901257480484, 900.5076691800019, 28.84638789990663], "id_box_line": 19, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 386.50901257480484, 900.5076691800019, 14.274877850162966], "text": "There are almost an infinite number of actions you can take, depending on the nature of the hazard or risk. For example, the pilot ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597066, "box": [61.5123935660151, 386.50901257480484, 900.5076691800019, 28.84638789990663], "id_box_line": 20, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 401.0805226245486, 635.3873775836729, 14.274877850162852], "text": "flying from point A to point B (50 miles) in MVFR conditions has several ways to reduce risk: ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597067, "box": [61.5123935660151, 313.27625274600405, 900.5760348883969, 58.0151863495189], "id_box_line": 15, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 313.27625274600405, 900.5760348883969, 14.274916672979316], "text": "The final step in risk management is mitigation, which is the payoff for accomplishing the entire risk management process and will ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597067, "box": [61.5123935660151, 313.27625274600405, 900.5760348883969, 58.0151863495189], "id_box_line": 16, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 327.8606260889327, 900.5309600691465, 14.274929613917948], "text": "often allow for mission accomplishment (the reason most pilots fly). By effectively mitigating known risks to acceptable levels, pilots ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597067, "box": [61.5123935660151, 313.27625274600405, 900.5760348883969, 58.0151863495189], "id_box_line": 17, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 342.43213613867636, 900.3971923384667, 14.274929613918175], "text": "can complete their planned flights safely or ensure that alternate options are selected for those rare occasions when the planned or ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597067, "box": [61.5123935660151, 313.27625274600405, 900.5760348883969, 58.0151863495189], "id_box_line": 18, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 357.01652242254363, 245.18186724950337, 14.274916672979316], "text": "ongoing flight cannot be completed. ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597068, "box": [61.5123935660151, 212.2980683281569, 900.5740925856356, 58.00232305633415], "id_box_line": 8, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 212.2980683281569, 900.4608529858624, 14.274916672979316], "text": "Assessing risk may be the most difficult part of risk management and applying the terms described above to specific risks takes some ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597068, "box": [61.5123935660151, 212.2980683281569, 900.5740925856356, 58.00232305633415], "id_box_line": 9, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 226.88244167108553, 900.377769310855, 14.274929613917948], "text": "practice. Once you have assessed risk likelihood and severity for all identified risks, you can readily classify the overall risk level for ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597068, "box": [61.5123935660151, 212.2980683281569, 900.5740925856356, 58.00232305633415], "id_box_line": 10, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 241.4539517208292, 512.4876847958549, 14.274929613918175], "text": "that hazard. For example, simply connecting the two factors as shown in ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597068, "box": [61.5123935660151, 212.2980683281569, 900.5740925856356, 58.00232305633415], "id_box_line": 11, "box_line": [576.8531704221037, 241.4539517208292, 79.08556198145402, 14.274929613918175], "text": "Figure 1-4 ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman,Italic", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597068, "box": [61.5123935660151, 212.2980683281569, 900.5740925856356, 58.00232305633415], "id_box_line": 12, "box_line": [658.1077655240998, 241.4539517208292, 303.97872062755096, 14.274929613918175], "text": "indicates the risk is high and the pilot may ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597068, "box": [61.5123935660151, 212.2980683281569, 900.5740925856356, 58.00232305633415], "id_box_line": 13, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 256.02546177057286, 659.6470069743369, 14.274929613918175], "text": "consider whether to not fly or fly only after finding ways to mitigate, eliminate, or control the risk. ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597069, "box": [61.51234165964821, 72.76885305406154, 900.457237958568, 43.43081300659037], "id_box_line": 1, "box_line": [61.5123935660151, 72.76885305406154, 900.4571860522011, 14.274916672979202], "text": "The next element is the severity or consequence of a pilot\u2019s action(s). It can relate to injury and/or damage. If the individual in the ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597069, "box": [61.51234165964821, 72.76885305406154, 900.457237958568, 43.43081300659037], "id_box_line": 2, "box_line": [61.51234165964821, 87.3403631038052, 900.4275006335353, 14.274916672979316], "text": "example above is not an instrument flight rules (IFR) pilot, what are the consequences of encountering inadvertent IMC? In this case, ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597069, "box": [61.51234165964821, 72.76885305406154, 900.457237958568, 43.43081300659037], "id_box_line": 3, "box_line": [61.51234165964821, 101.92474938767248, 779.7269801470356, 14.27491667297943], "text": "because the pilot is not IFR rated, the consequences could be fatal. The following are guidelines for this assignment. ", "category": "Text", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/Times New Roman", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597070, "box": [91.70515678279322, 129.10940427492847, 307.44927910755086, 16.621885336969513], "id_box_line": 4, "box_line": [91.70515678279322, 129.10940427492847, 307.44927910755086, 16.621885336969513], "text": "\u2981 $_{Catastrophic\u2014results in fatalities, total loss }$", "category": "List-item", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Segoe UI Symbol", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597071, "box": [91.70515678279322, 146.18254014847344, 272.3278573327818, 16.621885336969513], "id_box_line": 5, "box_line": [91.70515678279322, 146.18254014847344, 272.3278573327818, 16.621885336969513], "text": "\u2981 $_{Critical\u2014severe injury, major damage }$", "category": "List-item", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Segoe UI Symbol", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597072, "box": [91.70516348038895, 163.2387622149837, 280.95383486933974, 16.6218853369694], "id_box_line": 6, "box_line": [91.70516348038895, 163.2387622149837, 280.95383486933974, 16.6218853369694], "text": "\u2981 $_{Marginal\u2014minor injury, minor damage }$", "category": "List-item", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Segoe UI Symbol", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597073, "box": [91.70515678279322, 180.32065910410824, 463.8350417212023, 16.6218853369694], "id_box_line": 7, "box_line": [91.70515678279322, 180.32065910410824, 463.8350417212023, 16.6218853369694], "text": "\u2981 $_{Negligible\u2014less than minor injury, less than minor system damage }$", "category": "List-item", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Segoe UI Symbol", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597074, "box": [91.70515678279322, 430.3874008913466, 58.14621544103902, 16.62180769133647], "id_box_line": 21, "box_line": [91.70515678279322, 430.3874008913466, 58.14621544103902, 16.62180769133647], "text": "\u2981 $_{Drive. }$", "category": "List-item", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Segoe UI Symbol", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597075, "box": [91.70515678279322, 447.4734388808928, 531.3080945573752, 16.62180769133647], "id_box_line": 22, "box_line": [91.70515678279322, 447.4734388808928, 531.3080945573752, 16.62180769133647], "text": "\u2981 $_{Wait for the weather to improve to good visual flight rules (VFR) conditions. }$", "category": "List-item", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Segoe UI Symbol", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597076, "box": [91.70515678279322, 464.53369852031403, 288.91247736273897, 16.621807691336585], "id_box_line": 23, "box_line": [91.70515678279322, 464.53369852031403, 288.91247736273897, 16.621807691336585], "text": "\u2981 $_{Take a pilot who is rated as an IFR pilot. }$", "category": "List-item", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Segoe UI Symbol", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597077, "box": [91.70515678279322, 481.5939581597354, 124.30111278756102, 16.62180769133647], "id_box_line": 24, "box_line": [91.70515678279322, 481.5939581597354, 124.30111278756102, 16.62180769133647], "text": "\u2981 $_{Delay the flight. }$", "category": "List-item", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Segoe UI Symbol", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597078, "box": [91.70515678279322, 498.6670810923414, 130.95835550142226, 16.621807691336585], "id_box_line": 25, "box_line": [91.70515678279322, 498.6670810923414, 130.95835550142226, 16.621807691336585], "text": "\u2981 $_{Cancel the flight. }$", "category": "List-item", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Segoe UI Symbol", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597079, "box": [91.70515678279322, 589.3021554553948, 383.181170724051, 16.621807691336528], "id_box_line": 29, "box_line": [91.70515678279322, 589.3021554553948, 383.181170724051, 16.621807691336528], "text": "\u2981 $_{Book commercial flight/transfer the risk to the airlines. }$", "category": "List-item", "words": [], "linking": [], "font": {"color": [0, 0, 0, 255], "name": "/ABCDEE+Segoe UI Symbol", "size": 1}}, {"id_box": 597080, "box": [91.70515678279322, 606.358299876272, 380.81192972320616, 16.62180769133647], "id_box_line": 30, "box_line": [91.70515678279322, 606.358299876272, 380.81192972320616, 16.62180769133647], "text": "\u2981 $_{Change the date of the event to accommodat